9:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Frase and Jasper share a solid foundation of core features including Long Form, Short Form, Seo Tools, Templates. On the other hand, Jasper uniquely offers Tone Control and Plagiarism Check and Multilingual and Browser Extension, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Frase holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 6/10, while Jasper scores 8/10 overall and 7/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
a:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Frase offers a more budget-friendly entry point at $15/mo, compared to Jasper's starting price of $49/mo. Neither platform offers a free plan, so you will need to budget for at least the starting tier from the beginning. Be sure to take advantage of any trial periods they may offer."}]]}]
