d:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Frase is best suited for SEO content, content briefs, SERP analysis, content optimization, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Jasper, meanwhile, shines for marketing teams, ad copy, brand voice content, campaigns, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2016, Frase describes itself as \"AI-powered SEO content optimization and research tool.\" Jasper, established in 2021, positions itself as \"Enterprise AI marketing platform for brand-consistent content.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
e:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Jasper** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), more features (10 vs 6). However, this does not mean Frase is a poor choice — far from it. Frase excels in its own right, particularly for SEO content and content briefs.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value 50+ templates for marketing use cases, go with Jasper. If excellent serp analysis and content brief generation matters more to you, Frase is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
